  "_doc": [
    "Monthly climate averages for Orlando, FL (KORL — the airport station)",
    "used when a trip is beyond Open-Meteo's 10-day forecast horizon.",
    "",
    "Sourced from NOAA climate normals (1991–2020). Values are rounded for",
    "readability; see https://www.ncei.noaa.gov/products/climate-normals.",
    "",
    "Fields:",
    "  highF                  average daily high in °F",
    "  lowF                   average daily low in °F",
    "  precipitationProbability  fraction of days (0..1) with measurable rain",
    "  uvIndex                median peak UV index for the month",
    "  condition              single descriptive word the packing list + LLM can lean on",
    "",
    "Confidence is 'climatology' — distinct from the 'high/medium/low'",
    "labels used for live forecasts, so downstream code can flag 'this is",
    "a long-term average, not a real forecast'."
